# onSubmit and preventDefault

In React, you attach a submit handler to the `<form>` element with the `onSubmit` prop.

You must call `e.preventDefault()` to stop the browser from refreshing the page.

```jsx
const handleSubmit = (e) => {
  e.preventDefault();
  // Process the form data (e.g., send to API)
  console.log(formData);
};

<form onSubmit={handleSubmit}>
  {/* form fields */}
  <button type="submit">Submit</button>
</form>
```

Note: The submit button must have `type="submit"` (default for button inside a form).

